############ REACT JS INSTALL ############

# install node.js from official website (Lastest or high then 6).

# install lastest npm : (npm install --global npm) "in cmd".

# install create-react-app : (npm install --global create-react-app) "in cmd". (is a tool to make easy developpement an configure React-JS project)

>

############ CREATE REACT JS PROJECT ############

# Open CMD into your folder project and do : create-react-app (name of your project : without spaces and all be lower character).

# npm start : to start project.

# ( src/index.js & oublic/index.html ) : are used by CRA.

# Our files (CSS / JS / ...) Need to be inside "src" folder.

############ COMMANDES ############

# npm start : to start a project from the floder created by create-react-app, so your cmd need to be inside this folder.

# yarn : qui est une alternative à la commande officielle  npm . Yarn est un client alternatif, mais ses avantages se sont considérablement réduits depuis la sortie de npm 5.

# npm run build : Bundles the app into static files for production.

